:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15570:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add the sponsored link attribute to your affiliate links in WordPress?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, you might want to tell Google that a particular link is sponsored and that you’re getting paid or don’t want to vote for that link. It&#8217;s especially important if you&#8217;re partnering with different brands and have a lot of affiliate links on your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to easily add the sponsored link attribute to your affiliate links. We’ll also cover what the rel attribute is and when you should use it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick overview of the main topics of this post, so feel free to click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-the-rel-attribute-in-a-link-tag\">What Is the Rel Attribute in a Link Tag?</a></li><li><a href=\"#when-to-use-the-rel-attribute\">When to Use the Rel Attribute?</a></li><li><a href=\"#when-can-you-use-the-sponsored-link-attribute\">When Can You Use the Sponsored Link Attribute?</a></li><li><a href=\"#adding-the-sponsored-attribute-to-your-affiliate-links\">Adding the Sponsored Attribute to Your Affiliate Links </a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start with explaining what the rel attribute in a link tag is and how it looks.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-the-rel-attribute-in-a-link-tag\">What Is the Rel Attribute in a Link Tag?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you publish sponsored or affiliate links, chances are you’re already familiar with the rel=&#8221;nofollow&#8221; link tag. This tag is a common way of telling Google that you&#8217;re getting paid for adding a link on your blog or website or that you don&#8217;t want to vote for that link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year, Google evolved this further and introduced 2 new link attributes that we’ll introduce in a bit. But first, let’s take a look at the different parts of the rel attribute so that you can get an idea of how it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, the <strong>&lt;a&gt; </strong>tag defines a link, and you can customize that &lt;a&gt; tag with different styles or attributes. One of which is the<strong> rel </strong>attribute.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rel stands for relationship, and when you add the rel tag to your links, you’re telling Google that there’s a relationship between your site and the page you’re linking to.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, you can’t just type rel. You also need to assign a value to your rel attribute like in this example:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;a rel=\"sponsored\" href=\"https://www.example.com/\"&gt;sponsored link&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>With this attribute, you’re telling Google that your link is a sponsored link and that you might get paid from it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This takes us to the next question, when should you use rel attributes in your links?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s answer this next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"when-to-use-the-rel-attribute\">When to Use the Rel Attribute?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"421\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/when-to-use-link-attributes.png\" alt=\"When to use the rel attributes in your links\" class=\"wp-image-26601\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/when-to-use-link-attributes.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/when-to-use-link-attributes-300x179.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/when-to-use-link-attributes-600x358.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We all know that links are a big part of SEO, and especially backlinks. You can look at links as a type of currency. When you link to another website, Google sees it as you’re voting for the page you’re linking to.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if a website gets many votes or backlinks from authoritative and trusted sites, it will increase rankings in the search results. This, because Google sees your site as trustworthy when you get these backlinks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Evolution of Nofollow Links</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, all outbound or external links that you didn&#8217;t want to vote for were typically listed as nofollow. The nofollow attribute was meant to fight spam in the comment section of your website and was informing Google to ignore such links. For more details, check out our guide <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/\">on how to add nofollow links in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It later became one of the great ways as recommended by Google for flagging advertising or sponsored links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On March 1st, 2020, Google announced that it will begin formally reading link attributes on websites using the new standard of rel= to determine the nature of outbound links on a site. And that Google will count all rel attributes as hints for ranking purposes, rather than directives.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Nofollow: Joined By 2 New Link Attributes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This takes us back to September 2019 when Google introduced the 2 new rel attributes, which both evolved from the nofollow attribute.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>rel=&#8221;sponsored&#8221;: </strong>which should be used to identify links on your site that are created as part of advertisements, sponsorships, or other compensation agreements.</li><li><strong>rel=&#8221;ugc&#8221;</strong>: which is recommended for links within user generated content, such as reviews and forum posts. For more details, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-ugc-link-attribute-in-wordpress/\">how to add the ugc link attribute in WordPress</a>.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>In both cases, these work similarly to the original nofollow attribute since they also tell Google not to count the link as a vote. Google added these as options, but you can still just use nofollow with no penalty.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what the rel attributes are, let’s move on to when you can use the sponsored link attribute in your links.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"when-can-you-use-the-sponsored-link-attribute\">When Can You Use the Sponsored Link Attribute?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"320\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/affiliate-marketing-infographic.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-26877\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/affiliate-marketing-infographic.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/affiliate-marketing-infographic-300x132.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/affiliate-marketing-infographic-600x263.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add the sponsored link attribute to all links you’re getting paid from, often called affiliate links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Affiliate links are links that are assigned to you (<a href=\"https://www.chantelarnett.com/affiliate-marketing-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">like explained in the above image</a>) with a unique ID that you get from brands you’re partnering with and that you add to your website. And when someone clicks on your affiliate link and ends up buying the product you’re promoting, you’re getting paid a commission. If you haven&#8217;t already, you should check out <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/affiliates/\">how to make money with AIOSEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, it&#8217;s then good to tell Google about these paid links, which is when you can add the rel=&#8221;sponsored&#8221; attribute to your link. And when adding this attribute, you’re not voting or passing link juice to these affiliate links either.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s walk you through how to easily add the sponsored link attribute for your affiliate links in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"adding-the-sponsored-attribute-to-your-affiliate-links\">Adding the Sponsored Attribute to Your Affiliate Links&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to add the sponsored attribute to your affiliate links is by using the best WordPress SEO plugin, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO,&nbsp; you get all the advanced SEO tools you&#8217;ll need to optimize your site to rank high in search engines and drive more traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO offers powerful SEO tools and features like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Custom User Roles </strong>&nbsp;—&nbsp; custom user roles allow you to manage access to important SEO features without handing over control of your website.</li><li><strong>SEO Audit Checklist </strong>— analyze your entire WordPress site to detect critical errors and get actionable insights to boost your SEO and get more traffic.</li><li><strong>Smart XML Sitemaps</strong> — automatically generate a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">WordPress XML sitemap</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress\">video sitemap</a> to notify all search engines of any new content.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These are just a few of all the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\">great features</a> that can take your SEO efforts to the next level.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s get back to the topic of how to add the sponsored link attribute to your affiliate links.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Adding Rel=&#8221;Sponsored&#8221; to Your Links Using AIOSEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, you first need to install and activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">AIOSEO plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"439\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/alll-in-one-seo-dashboard.png\" alt=\"The best WordPress SEO plugin All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25715\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/alll-in-one-seo-dashboard.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/alll-in-one-seo-dashboard-300x180.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/alll-in-one-seo-dashboard-600x361.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t installed a plugin before, please visit WPBeginner’s step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, head over to your blog post or page’s editing page. Add the <strong>anchor text</strong> for your affiliate link (marked in blue below), select the anchor text, and click on the link icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"285\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"How to add the sponsored link attribute to your affiliate links\" class=\"wp-image-26602\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-300x121.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-704x285.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-600x242.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, simply insert your affiliate link in the window and click on <strong>Add “sponsored” to link</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Add &quot;sponsored&quot; to link in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26603\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-300x235.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-600x470.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once the sponsored attribute is added to your link, you’ll see the Add “sponsored” to link button turn blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Enable add &quot;sponsored&quot; to link in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26605\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sponsored-links-in-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-300x235.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sponsored-links-in-wordpress-600x470.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, press <strong>Enter </strong>on your keyboard and your affiliate link is added.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With just a few clicks, you’ve now added the sponsored attribute to your affiliate link and told Google and other search engine bots not to vote for that link and that you’re actually getting paid from it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Combine Link Attributes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One more thing…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;you can also combine several rel attributes in one link.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why should you do that you may think?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not all search engines support the sponsored and ugc rel attributes. So then it’s good to also use nofollow along with the sponsored or ugc attributes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-several-rel-attributes-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Combine several rel attributes to your links in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26606\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-several-rel-attributes-in-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-several-rel-attributes-in-wordpress-300x235.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/adding-several-rel-attributes-in-wordpress-600x470.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That completes it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this blog post helped you learn how to add the sponsored link attribute to your affiliate links.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you go, you may also want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/\">how to add nofollow links</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-ugc-link-attribute-in-wordpress/\">how to add ugc attribute in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to learn how to optimize your blog post like a pro, you should check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" title=\"Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2021\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using AIOSEO yet?<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"> </a>What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-the-sponsored-link-attribute-to-your-affiliate-links/\">How to Add the Sponsored Link Attribute to Your Affiliate Links</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-the-sponsored-link-attribute-to-your-affiliate-links/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Create a Video Sitemap in WordPress [The Easy Way]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:174:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 04 Feb 2021 13:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"how to create a video sitemap in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"video sitemap generator\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Video XML Sitemap\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"wordpress video sitemap plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=26411\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:541:\"<p>Have you spent time, effort, and money into creating a video but no one seems to find it in search? If so, you need to help the search engines to find your video with a video sitemap. In this post, we’ll show you how to create a video sitemap in WordPress using the best video sitemap generator plugin in the market.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">How to Create a Video Sitemap in WordPress [The Easy Way]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17429:\"<p>Have you spent time, effort, and money into creating a video but no one seems to find it in the search results? If so, you need to help Google to find your video by creating a video sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Video is something you can’t ignore as a marketing and SEO tool. In fact, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">87%</a> of video marketers say video has increased traffic to their website, and 80% say it directly helped to increase sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is why you need to make sure your videos are found by search engines. So in this post, we’ll show you how to create a video sitemap in WordPress using the best video sitemap generator plugin on the market.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#why-should-you-use-video-to-boost-seo\">Why Should You Use Video to Boost SEO?</a></li><li><a href=\"#what-is-a-video-xml-sitemap\">What Is a Video XML Sitemap?</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-should-you-create-a-video-sitemap\">Why Should You Create a Video Sitemap?</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-the-best-video-sitemap-generator-plugin-aioseo\">Use the Best Video Sitemap Generator Plugin AIOSEO</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we dive into how to create a video sitemap, let’s take a quick look&nbsp;at why you should use video on your website to boost SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-should-you-use-video-to-boost-seo\">Why Should You Use Video to Boost SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Video is vital to your business’s growth and for gaining brand recognition online. If used correctly, video can be an extremely powerful form of content and make a significant contribution to your overall SEO strategy, in more ways than one.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that you’re <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">53</a> times more likely to show up first on Google if you&#8217;ve got a video embedded on your site? Google will also crawl your page faster if it sees you have a video on it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One thing’s for sure; video isn’t going anywhere. By 2021, Cisco says, video will represent <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/content-marketing-statistics/#video\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">82%</a> of all internet traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"363\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Screenshot-2018-4-10-5-Online-Video-Trends-to-Inform-Your-2017-Media-Plan.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-26423\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Screenshot-2018-4-10-5-Online-Video-Trends-to-Inform-Your-2017-Media-Plan.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Screenshot-2018-4-10-5-Online-Video-Trends-to-Inform-Your-2017-Media-Plan-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Screenshot-2018-4-10-5-Online-Video-Trends-to-Inform-Your-2017-Media-Plan-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from these amazing stats, adding video to your website can also help with:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Increasing Your CTR (Click Through Rate)</strong> — including video on your site drives a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">157%</a> increase in organic traffic.</li><li><strong>Lowering Your Bounce Rate</strong> — people spend over twice as long on a page with video than without.</li><li><strong>Help You Get More Quality Backlinks </strong>— the higher the quality of your content, the more likely you are to get quality backlinks.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This is all great, but if your videos aren’t popping up in search results, what can you do? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s what we’re going to show you after we’ve first explained what a video XML sitemap is and why you should create one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-video-xml-sitemap\">What Is a Video XML Sitemap?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first: what’s a video XML sitemap? And what does it do?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A video sitemap is a specially formatted file that lists all pages on your website that contain videos. It&#8217;s generally made for bots, not people. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With a video sitemap, you can inform Google of the category, title, description, running time, and audience for each video that you’ve added to your site. This helps Google know about all video content on your site, which greatly improves your chances of improving rankings in the video search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, video sitemaps allow search engines to better index and crawl your site for video content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-should-you-create-a-video-sitemap\">Why Should You Create a Video Sitemap?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The answer to why you should create a video sitemap is pretty self-explanatory. Let&#8217;s start by the fact that <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">93%</a> of online experiences start with a search and Google’s algorithms increasingly prioritize websites with video content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like you probably understand, it&#8217;s then crucial that search engines find your videos, and the faster the better. That’s where a video sitemap comes into the picture.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, we do need to clarify that search engines can still index your video content and show it in search results even if it’s not included in your video sitemap. It just makes the process a lot faster than waiting on Google to naturally find your video content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know why you should create one, let&#8217;s show you how to create a video sitemap in WordPress the easy way so that you can show up faster in the video search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"use-the-best-video-sitemap-generator-plugin-aioseo\">Use the Best Video Sitemap Generator Plugin AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO The Best WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-23910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using a video sitemap generator plugin for WordPress like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO</a>) is the best way to automatically create a video sitemap.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AISOEO will notify Google of all new video content added to your site, which will help you rank higher in video search on Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, it’s super easy! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, if you have the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro version</a> the video sitemap is enabled by default and there’s very little configuration needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to mention, with AIOSEO you’ll get access to many <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\">advanced SEO tools</a> to help you improve your SEO and increase rankings in search engines. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s show you how to easily create a video XML sitemap that’ll be automatically sent to the video search results on Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Your Video Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, go to <strong>Sitemaps</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, and then click on the <strong>Video Sitemap</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to create a video sitemap in WordPress (the easy way) using All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26412\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you’ll see the video sitemap screen, and you need to make sure that the <strong>Enable Sitemap</strong> button is set to on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"176\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to create a video sitemap in WordPress (the easy way) - enable video sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26414\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x72.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x145.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The blue button means you’re all set.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>View Your Video Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, if you want to view your video sitemap, you can click on the <strong>Open Sitemap </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"137\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to create a video sitemap in WordPress (the easy way) - open sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26415\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x56.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x113.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve opened your sitemap, you’ll see an index page for your video sitemap that looks like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"323\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Video XML sitemap index in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26416\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x265.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This index page lists all of the video sitemaps for your site. And each video sitemap contains a different type of content. For example, from the above screenshot you can see video sitemaps for posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, you can click on each link in the index to see a list of your video content for that post or page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to view your video sitemap, let’s take a look at how to include and exclude content of your video sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Include Content in Your Video Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, you need to decide what content you want to include in your video sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you want to include all your content, you can leave the <strong>Include All Post Types</strong> and Include <strong>All Taxonomies </strong>check boxes set to checked.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, if you uncheck these boxes, you’ll see a list of all your content Post Types and Taxonomies and can select which to include in your sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"287\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/post-types-and-taxonomies-for-video-sitemap-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Post types and taxonomies for video sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26418\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/post-types-and-taxonomies-for-video-sitemap-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/post-types-and-taxonomies-for-video-sitemap-in-aioseo-300x118.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/post-types-and-taxonomies-for-video-sitemap-in-aioseo-600x236.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Exclude Content from Your Video Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to exclude content from your video sitemap, you can do this by navigating to the <strong>Advanced Settings </strong>tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"197\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-settings-for-video-sitemaps-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Advanced settings for video sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26419\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-settings-for-video-sitemaps-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-settings-for-video-sitemaps-in-aioseo-300x81.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-settings-for-video-sitemaps-in-aioseo-600x162.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can choose which posts or pages you don’t want to include in your video sitemap.&nbsp;Simply enter the title of any post or page and a drop down will appear that shows matching content. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"299\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/typing-in-the-exclude-posts-pages-field-1024x299.gif\" alt=\"Exclude posts and pages for video sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26420\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/typing-in-the-exclude-posts-pages-field-1024x299.gif 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/typing-in-the-exclude-posts-pages-field-300x88.gif 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/typing-in-the-exclude-posts-pages-field-768x224.gif 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/typing-in-the-exclude-posts-pages-field-600x175.gif 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the content you want to exclude and it will be removed from your video sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Any content that’s been set to be excluded from the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/showing-or-hiding-your-content-in-search-results/\">Show in Search Results</a> in Search Appearance won’t show up in this drop down list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you’re almost finished!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just two more things…</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Sitemap Indexes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have more than 1000 URLs in your sitemap, we recommend that you set the <strong>Enable Sitemap Indexes</strong> option to <strong>Enabled.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"96\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitemap-indexes-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png\" alt=\"Enable sitemap indexes for video sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26421\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitemap-indexes-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitemap-indexes-in-all-in-one-seo-1-300x39.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitemap-indexes-in-all-in-one-seo-1-600x79.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help organize your sitemap entries into distinct files in your sitemap.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’ve included your videos using custom fields, you can see <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/including-videos-in-custom-fields-in-your-video-sitemap/\">how to add them to your video sitemap here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this blog post helped answer all your questions about video sitemaps and how to easily create a video XML sitemap for your WordPress site. Before you know it, your videos will start ranking higher in the video search results on Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One last thing before you go&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Is your site too slow? If so, you may also want to check out WPBeginner’s guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-performance-speed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to boost WordPress speed and performance</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">the best WordPress sitemap plugin</a> do the heavy lifting for you. If you’re still not sure which SEO plugin to choose, you’ll know after reading our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-which-is-the-best-seo-plugin/\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO</a> post.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for AIOSEO’s new features and improvements.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">How to Create a Video Sitemap in WordPress [The Easy Way]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"Introducing Product and FAQ Schema, and More: Boost Your SEO with Powerful Rich Snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 02 Feb 2021 13:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"FAQ schema markup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"product rich snippet\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"product schema markup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"recipe schema markup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"software application schema\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=25917\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:517:\"<p>You’ve probably seen those nice looking rich search results with star ratings and prices or questions and answers. With our latest Schema Pro update, you can seamlessly tell Google to show these rich results for your products, FAQs, apps, courses, and recipes to boost SEO.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more/\">Introducing Product and FAQ Schema, and More: Boost Your SEO with Powerful Rich Snippets</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11396:\"<p>You’ve probably seen those nice looking rich search results with star ratings and prices or questions and answers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, we know you&#8217;ve been asking for it…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>….and guess what, look no further!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With our latest Schema Pro update, you can seamlessly tell Google to show these rich results for your products, FAQs, apps, courses, and delicious recipes.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, it will unlock the highest rankings and traffic for your site without you having to be an SEO expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a closer look…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Boost SEO with Adding Schema Markup to Your Site</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first: what’s Schema Markup? And what does it do?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema Markup (also called structured data) is used by all big search engines like Google, Bing, Yahoo, and Yandex to show additional information in their search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It creates nice looking rich snippets or rich results that give direct information to users about what a page is about, as well as make it look better in search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of a rich snippet that Google displays when Product Schema is added to your site:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-1.png\" alt=\"Introducing product and FAQ schema: boost your SEO with powerful rich snippets\" class=\"wp-image-25918\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-1-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-1-600x334.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, it makes your content look a lot better in search and includes all the information needed to spike people’s interest.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But that’s not all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rich snippets also increase the CTR (Click Through Rate) to your site since they look more appealing and give additional information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And like you probably already know, more clicks will eventually lead to higher rankings and more conversions as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, it’s a great way of boosting your SEO, getting more organic traffic, and increasing sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s take a closer look at the different Markups next, starting with Product Schema.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Product Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Like we briefly touched on earlier, Product Schema tells Google to show rich product results that include star ratings and prices.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s another example of a rich snippet for products:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"189\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"Rich snippet for products in search results on Google\" class=\"wp-image-25919\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-rich-snippet-example.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-rich-snippet-example-300x80.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-rich-snippet-example-704x189.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-rich-snippet-example-600x161.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, it shows star ratings, price, and even if the product is in stock or not. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you&#8217;re doing an image search on Google, it will show these rich results as well: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-image-rich-snippet-example-1.png\" alt=\"Rich snippet for products in image results on Google\" class=\"wp-image-26215\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-image-rich-snippet-example-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-image-rich-snippet-example-1-300x198.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/product-image-rich-snippet-example-1-600x396.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This gives people the sneak peek they’ll need to decide if they want to see more information about the product and click through to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did we say that the Product Schema is integrated with both <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WooCommerce </a>and <a href=\"https://easydigitaldownloads.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">EDD</a>? So if you have an <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-start-an-online-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">online store</a>, you should definitely use it to get these nice looking product rich results.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>FAQ Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next awesome feature is FAQ Schema. It tells Google to show a rich snippet with a list of questions and answers for your page. This is very useful for people searching for information and need quick answers to their questions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, unlike most SEO changes, it doesn’t take months or years to see results from this. You can literally see results in less than 30 minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s pretty awesome!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can look like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"804\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/faq-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"FAQ rich snippet in search results on Google\" class=\"wp-image-25921\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/faq-rich-snippet-example.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/faq-rich-snippet-example-263x300.png 263w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/faq-rich-snippet-example-600x683.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It will show a collapsible list in the search results on Google. And when a question is clicked, the answer is displayed in a dropdown window.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like in this example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"378\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/expanded-faq-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"Expanded FAQ rich snippet in search results on Google\" class=\"wp-image-25922\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/expanded-faq-rich-snippet-example.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/expanded-faq-rich-snippet-example-300x155.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/expanded-faq-rich-snippet-example-600x311.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Software Application Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you an app developer or do you sell software? If so, you should add Software Application Schema to your site. It allows you to show your app details in search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of a rich snippet for apps:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"188\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/app-rich-snippet-example-2.png\" alt=\"Software application rich snippet in search results on Google\" class=\"wp-image-26197\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/app-rich-snippet-example-2.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/app-rich-snippet-example-2-300x77.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/app-rich-snippet-example-2-600x155.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Obviously, this is a great feature when people search for the latest apps on Google. It shows additional information such as price, ratings, platforms, and the app types straight from search.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Course Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you offer education or courses on your website, the Course Schema is perfect for you. Not only can prospective students easily find you on Google, but you can also provide more information such as the course name, who&#8217;s offering it, and a short description.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can look like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"548\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/cource-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-26194\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/cource-rich-snippet-example.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/cource-rich-snippet-example-300x225.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/cource-rich-snippet-example-600x450.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rich snippet shows a professional overview of each course, and you can click on the arrow to the right to read more information. It gives people access to all this information straight from the search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Recipe Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, our last feature for this Schema Pro update is for the food and bakery lover who shares their recipes online. The Recipe Schema shows your delicious recipes on Google. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Who can resist?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"358\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-26196\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet-600x294.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These yummy rich snippets show your image, star ratings, and even how long it takes to bake them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you excited yet? You should be!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine what this can do for your rankings in search engines&#8230;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>…best of all, AIOSEO makes this easy as 1-2-3. No need to spend hours studying SEO or buy expensive software.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget, with AIOSEO you can also add <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/rich-snippets-schema/\">Schema Markup</a> to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Articles</li><li>Pages</li><li>Categories&nbsp;</li><li>Tags&nbsp;</li><li>Breadcrumbs</li><li>Sitelinks Search Boxes</li><li>Social Profile Links</li><li>And more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you’ll love these new Schema Markups. In adding them, our goal was to help you take your SEO efforts to the next level.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So go ahead, give it a try, and you’ll dominate the rich search results on Google in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t have the AIOSEO Pro license yet? <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Click here to upgrade</a> and unlock all powerful SEO tools and features.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more/\">Introducing Product and FAQ Schema, and More: Boost Your SEO with Powerful Rich Snippets</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-product-and-faq-schema-and-more/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"How to Easily Edit a Robots.txt File in WordPress (Step by Step)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:148:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 28 Jan 2021 16:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"all in one seo robots.txt\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"edit robots.txt wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"how to edit robots.txt in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"robots.txt wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"wordpress robots.txt\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=26293\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:443:\"<p>Do you want to know how to edit a robots.txt file in WordPress? In this post, we\'ll show you how to easily edit your robots.txt file in WordPress step by step. We\'ll also cover what a robots.txt file is and why it\'s important.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/\">How to Easily Edit a Robots.txt File in WordPress (Step by Step)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18052:\"<p>Do you want to know how to edit a robots.txt file in WordPress? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A robots.txt file is a powerful SEO tool since it works as a website guide for search engine crawl bots or robots. Telling bots to not crawl unnecessary pages can increase the load speed of your site and improve rankings in search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll show you how to edit your robots.txt file in WordPress step by step. We&#8217;ll also cover what a robots.txt file is and why it&#8217;s important.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-a-robots-txt-file\">What Is a Robots.txt File?</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-is-the-robots-txt-file-important\">Why Is the Robots.txt File Important?</a></li><li><a href=\"#edit-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress-using-aioseo\">Edit Robots.txt in WordPress Using AIOSEO</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-robots-txt-file\">What Is a Robots.txt File?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A robots.txt file tells search engines how to crawl your site — where they&#8217;re allowed to go or not. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines like Google use these web crawlers, sometimes called web robots, to archive and categorize websites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most bots are configured to search for a robots.txt file on the server before it reads any other file from your site. It does this to see if you&#8217;ve added special instructions on how to crawl and index your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And the robots.txt file is typically stored in the root directory, also known as the main folder of your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The URL can look like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>http:&#47;&#47;www.example.com/robots.txt\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>To check the robots.txt file for your own website, you simply replace the <strong>http://www.example.com/</strong> with your domain and add <strong>robots.txt </strong>at the end. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s take a look at how the basic format for a robots.txt file looks like:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>User-agent: &#91;user-agent name]\nDisallow: &#91;URL string not to be crawled]\n \nUser-agent: &#91;user-agent name]\nAllow: &#91;URL string to be crawled]\n \nSitemap: &#91;URL of your XML Sitemap]\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>For this to make any sense, we first need to explain what <strong>User-agent</strong> means. It&#8217;s basically the name of the search engine bot or robot that you want to block or allow to crawl your site (for example the Googlebot crawler). </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Second, you can include multiple instructions to either <strong>Allow</strong> or <strong>Disallow</strong> specific URLs, plus adding multiple sitemaps. Like you&#8217;ve probably figured out, the disallow option tells search engine bots not to crawl these URLs.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Default Robots.txt File in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, WordPress automatically creates a robots.txt file for your site. So even if you don’t lift a finger, your site should already have the default WordPress robots.txt file. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But when you later customize it with your own rules, the default content is replaced.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s how the default WordPress robots.txt file looks:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>User-agent: *\nDisallow: /wp-admin/\nAllow: /wp-admin/admin-ajax.php\n\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>The asterisk after <strong>User-agent: * </strong>means that the robots.txt file is for all web robots that visit your site. And like mentioned, the <strong>Disallow: /wp-admin/</strong> tells robots to not visit your wp-admin page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can test your robots.txt file by adding <strong>/robots.txt</strong> at the end of your domain name. For example, if you enter “https://aioseo.com/robots.txt” in your web browser it shows the robots.txt file for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"280\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-robots-txt-file.png\" alt=\"The robots.txt file for All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26295\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-robots-txt-file.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-robots-txt-file-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-robots-txt-file-600x230.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what a robots.txt file is and the basics of how it works, let’s take a look at why the robots.txt file matters in the first place.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-is-the-robots-txt-file-important\">Why Is the Robots.txt File Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots_txt_file_explained.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"576\" height=\"459\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots_txt_file_explained.png\" alt=\"How to easily edit a robots.txt file in WordPress (step by step)\" class=\"wp-image-26334\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots_txt_file_explained.png 576w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots_txt_file_explained-300x239.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The robots.txt file is important if you want to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Optimize Your Site Load Speed</strong> — by telling bots to not waste time on pages you don’t want them to crawl and index, you can free up resources and increase your site load speed. </li><li><strong>Optimizing Your Server Usage</strong> — blocking bots that are wasting resources, will clean up your server and reduce 404 errors.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>When to Use the Meta Noindex Tag Instead&nbsp;of Robots.txt</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if your primary goal is to stop certain pages from being included in search engine results, the proper approach is to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-hide-a-wordpress-page-from-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">use a meta noindex tag</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is because the robots.txt is not directly telling search engines not to index content – it’s just telling them not to crawl it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, you can use robots.txt to add specific rules for how search engines and other bots interact with your site, but it won’t explicitly control whether your content is indexed or not.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s show you how to easily edit your robots.txt file in WordPress step by step using AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"edit-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress-using-aioseo\">Edit Robots.txt in WordPress Using AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to edit the robots.txt file is by using the best WordPress SEO plugin, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>. It allows you to take control of your website and configure a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/robots-editor/\" title=\"Robots.txt Editor\">robots.txt</a> file that will override the default WordPress file.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you didn&#8217;t know this already, AIOSEO is a complete WordPress SEO plugin, which lets you optimize your content for search engines and increase rankings with just a few clicks. Check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\">powerful SEO tools and features here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Custom Robots.txt</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started editing your robots.txt file, click on <strong>Tools</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, and then click on the <strong>Robots.txt Editor</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"334\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/tools-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to edit a robots.txt file in WordPress using AIOSEO (step by step)\" class=\"wp-image-26296\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/tools-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/tools-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x137.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/tools-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x275.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will then generate a dynamic robots.txt file. Its content is stored in your WordPress database and can be viewed in your web browser as we&#8217;ll show you in a bit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve entered the <strong>Robots.txt Editor</strong>, you need to <strong>Enable Custom Robots.txt</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"379\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-custom-robots-txt-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to edit a robots.txt file in WordPress using AIOSEO - enable custom robots.txt\" class=\"wp-image-26297\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-custom-robots-txt-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-custom-robots-txt-in-all-in-one-seo-300x156.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-custom-robots-txt-in-all-in-one-seo-600x312.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the button so it turns blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll then see the <strong>Robots.txt Preview</strong> section at the bottom of the screen, which shows the WordPress default rules that you can overwrite with your own.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"263\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-preview-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Robots.txt preview in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26298\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-preview-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-preview-in-all-in-one-seo-300x108.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-preview-in-all-in-one-seo-600x216.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The default rules tell robots not to crawl your core WordPress files (admin pages). It’s also recommended to not crawl plugins and themes. They don’t include any relevant content and are unnecessary for search engines to crawl.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s move on to how you can add your own rules using the rule builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Adding Rules Using the Rule Builder</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The rule builder is used to add your own custom rules for what pages the robots should crawl or not.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, if you&#8217;d like to add a rule that blocks all robots from a temp directory (meaning a temporary folder on for example a hard drive), you can use the rule builder to do this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like in this example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-rule-builder-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Adding robots.txt rules in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26299\" width=\"730\" height=\"130\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-rule-builder-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-rule-builder-in-all-in-one-seo-300x53.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-rule-builder-in-all-in-one-seo-600x107.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a custom rule, simply enter the User Agent (for example Googlebot crawler) in the <strong>User Agent</strong> field. Or you can use the * symbol that will make your rule apply to all user agents (robots).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, select either <strong>Allow</strong> or <strong>Disallow</strong> to allow or block the User Agent.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-add-rule-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Disallow or allow robots to crawl your site in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26300\" width=\"730\" height=\"138\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-add-rule-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-add-rule-in-all-in-one-seo-300x57.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/robots-txt-add-rule-in-all-in-one-seo-600x113.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After you&#8217;ve decided what bots to allow or disallow, you need to enter the directory path or filename in the <strong>Directory Path</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once this is done, you can go ahead and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button in the right bottom corner of the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to add more rules, you can click the <strong>Add Rule</strong> button and repeat the steps above.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t forget to save your changes when you’re done.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, when you’ve saved your new rules, they&#8217;ll appear in the <strong>Robots.txt Preview</strong> section. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"379\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/preview-custom-robots-text-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Robots.txt preview in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26303\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/preview-custom-robots-text-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/preview-custom-robots-text-in-all-in-one-seo-300x156.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/preview-custom-robots-text-in-all-in-one-seo-600x312.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To view your robots.txt file, you simply click on the <strong>Open Robots.txt</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-robot-txt-file-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"112\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-robot-txt-file-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Open robots.txt in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26302\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-robot-txt-file-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-robot-txt-file-in-all-in-one-seo-300x46.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-robot-txt-file-in-all-in-one-seo-600x92.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s take a look at how you can edit your rules next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Editing Rules Using the Rule Builder</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To edit your rules, you can just change the details in the rule builder and click on the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"615\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing-a-custom-rule-in-the-robots.txt-editor-1024x615.gif\" alt=\"Editing a robots.txt file rule in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26301\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing-a-custom-rule-in-the-robots.txt-editor-1024x615.gif 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing-a-custom-rule-in-the-robots.txt-editor-300x180.gif 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing-a-custom-rule-in-the-robots.txt-editor-768x461.gif 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing-a-custom-rule-in-the-robots.txt-editor-600x360.gif 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s very easy! And so is deleting rules like we&#8217;ll show you next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Deleting a Rule in the Rule Builder</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To delete a rule, simply click the trash can icon to the right of the rule.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/delete-custom-rule-in-robots-txt-editor-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Deleting a robots.txt rule in the rule builder of All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26304\" width=\"730\" height=\"167\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/delete-custom-rule-in-robots-txt-editor-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/delete-custom-rule-in-robots-txt-editor-in-aioseo-300x69.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/delete-custom-rule-in-robots-txt-editor-in-aioseo-600x137.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As simple as that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before leaving this topic, we want to let you know that in case you need to edit your robots.txt file for multisite networks, you can check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/robots-txt-editor-for-multisite-networks/\">documentation on how to do that here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this tutorial showed you how to easily edit a robots.txt file in WordPress. Now, go ahead and add your own rules, and you’ll make sure your website is optimized for optimal performance in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One more thing&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;do you think Google Search Console is confusing? It doesn’t have to be!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">how to easily verIfy your WordPress site using AIOSEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re looking for great ways to improve your SEO to drive even more traffic to your site, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for AIOSEO’s new features and improvements.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/\">How to Easily Edit a Robots.txt File in WordPress (Step by Step)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"How to Add UGC Link Attribute in WordPress (In Just 2 Clicks)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:148:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-ugc-link-attribute-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-ugc-link-attribute-in-wordpr