ttp://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49127:\"<p>Are you looking for the best SEO plugin for WordPress? If you are, then you’ve likely narrowed your choice down to the two most popular WordPress SEO plugins: All in One SEO (AIOSEO) and Yoast SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both of these SEO plugins help you optimize your WordPress website and improve your rankings in search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But which one is better?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t worry, we’ll help you to figure this out!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll compare Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO, and show you the major differences that matter. As well as give you our verdict of which of the two is the best SEO plugin for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But first, let&#8217;s explain what an SEO plugin is and why you should use one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Is an SEO Plugin?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO plugins allow website owners to easily optimize their sites for search engines. You can easily add metadata, as well as more advanced SEO features, such as <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">XML sitemaps</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\">schema markup</a>, and robots.txt files to your web pages. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This, to improve rankings and drive more traffic to your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yoast SEO and All in One SEO are SEO plugins for WordPress. That means you install them as plugins on your website, and they let you optimize your site for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://yoast.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/ZK_csKtIBMoxVZzw3s6hmZAJeR5ty3gjIbrVHLfKDeESPQI7Gpu75JsDgQAc0MRpzc7aq-Pe1A_hOR12TgBOdS5aJ20L8sIAF9kzofPn-wbLQanyrvLUF1Kfyoi5TJ2A5S8N9Ijx\" alt=\"Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO - Yoast SEO for Everyone\"/></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO offers a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-seo-pack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">free version</a>, as well as <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">4 paid versions</a>. It’s one of the top 14 most popular WordPress plugins on WordPress.org with over 2+ million active installations.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png\" alt=\"Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO - All in One SEO (AIOSEO) The Best WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-23910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re going to look at the similarities and major differences between Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO next.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO: SEO Plugins Compared</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Since this is a comprehensive post, feel free to use our table of content to jump to the sections you want:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#getting-started-with-yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo\">Getting Started with Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO</a></li><li><a href=\"#seo-audit-checklist\">SEO Audit Checklist</a></li><li><a href=\"#on-page-optimization\">On Page Optimization</a></li><li><a href=\"#additional-seo-tools-and-features\">Additional SEO Tools and Features</a></li><li><a href=\"#paid-plans-and-pricing\">Paid Plans and Pricing</a></li><li><a href=\"#yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-support\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO Support</a></li><li><a href=\"#yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-which-is-best\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO: Which Is Best?</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you a beginner? Let’s look at how easy it is to get started with these SEO plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"getting-started-with-yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo\">Getting Started with Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started with an SEO plugin, they have so-called configuration or setup wizards that help you with your SEO settings. Let&#8217;s take a look at the differences in the configuration for both contenders.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Installation Wizards Compared</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yoast SEO has a 12 step installation wizard, and it gets pretty overwhelming. It throws the beginner into a complicated and cluttered dashboard with more technical information than necessary when just starting out. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is what you&#8217;ll see after <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">installing and activating</a> Yoast SEO. It&#8217;s an overview of the Yoast SEO Dashboard, and so far it looks okay.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/general-dashboard-yoast-seo.png\" alt=\"Yoast SEO dashboard general settings\" class=\"wp-image-24635\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/general-dashboard-yoast-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/general-dashboard-yoast-seo-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/general-dashboard-yoast-seo-600x281.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Under the General settings tab, you can find a first-time SEO configuration wizard. It&#8217;s after clicking on this wizard that you get a knot in your stomach.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-wizard-yoast-seo.png\" alt=\"Yoast SEO installation wizard\" class=\"wp-image-24636\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-wizard-yoast-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-wizard-yoast-seo-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-wizard-yoast-seo-600x283.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While Yoast SEO&#8217;s configuration wizard has 12 steps and feels technical and complicated, AIOSEO&#8217;s setup wizard only has 4 steps that are easy to follow. It looks much cleaner and is straightforward and beginner-friendly. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO has outdone itself to simplify things and make it easier for users to set up their SEO settings. Let&#8217;s take a look at the setup wizard next.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">installing and activating AIOSEO</a>, you’ll see the<strong> </strong>General Settings tab in the All in One SEO menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"390\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-dashboard-general-settings.png\" alt=\"All in One SEO (AIOSEO) dashboard general settings\" class=\"wp-image-24632\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-dashboard-general-settings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-dashboard-general-settings-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-dashboard-general-settings-600x321.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see an overview of the AIOSEO Dashboard,<strong> </strong>and you can launch the Setup Wizard with a single click. There’s also a video to watch that helps users understand the setup process before they start.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In General Settings, you have the option to switch between three more tabs. The Webmaster Tools tab is especially useful since it allows you to submit your site to search engines such as Google, Bing, Yandex, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"433\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-wizard.png\" alt=\"All in One SEO (AIOSEO) setup wizard\" class=\"wp-image-24633\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-wizard.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-wizard-300x178.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-wizard-600x356.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you&#8217;re able to categorize your site, as well as set up the Home Page Title and Meta Description. AIOSEO makes this easy and beginner-friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In contrast to Yoast SEO, All in One SEO has lots of pre-installed tags with different variables that you can use for your homepage&#8217;s title and description. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"662\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-home-page-title-and-description.png\" alt=\"All in One SEO (AIOSEO) home page title and meta description setting\" class=\"wp-image-24634\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-home-page-title-and-description.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-home-page-title-and-description-300x272.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-setup-home-page-title-and-description-600x544.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you can click on the + Site Title tag and it will give you variables that will automatically be added to your title, such as Author Last Name, Author First Name, Post Day, Post Date, and much more.&nbsp;These are options that Yoast SEO doesn&#8217;t have.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget, the + Current Year tag, which is an incredible feature to easily add the year to your SEO title.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/current-year-title-tag-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"144\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/current-year-title-tag-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"The current year title tag in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25328\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/current-year-title-tag-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/current-year-title-tag-in-all-in-one-seo-300x59.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/current-year-title-tag-in-all-in-one-seo-600x118.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, AIOSEO has many more great SEO features, which help make the optimization process easier. It&#8217;s leaps ahead of Yoast SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, to something even more exciting! The SEO audit checklist tool in AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"seo-audit-checklist\">SEO Audit Checklist </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"472\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard.png\" alt=\"New dashboard with SEO site score in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25806\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard.png 800w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard-768x453.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-new-dashboard-600x354.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/seo-audit-checklist/\">SEO audit checklist</a> is a fantastic tool and is something that’s unique to All in One SEO!&nbsp;Yoast SEO doesn&#8217;t have anything like it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is what will take your SEO efforts to another level. Best of all, it&#8217;s a great tool for beginners who don&#8217;t know that much about SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It lets you analyze your website in seconds and identifies critical errors that could inhibit rankings in search engines. And it also gives you the ability to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">analyze your competitors’ SEO</a>, so you can find out what keywords they’re using.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To clarify, the SEO audit checklist lets you:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Follow its SEO audit checklist to optimize your website’s settings</li><li>Identify any critical errors that could be harming your rankings</li><li>Get recommended SEO improvements</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started analyzing your site, you simply visit the All in One SEO<strong> </strong>menu and go to the SEO Analysis<strong> </strong>tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"439\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO SEO Audit Checklist\" class=\"wp-image-21803\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis-300x180.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis-600x361.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can check your SEO site score.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"731\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score-1024x731.png\" alt=\"SEO Audit Checklist in All in One SEO \" class=\"wp-image-25807\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score-1024x731.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score-300x214.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score-768x548.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score-600x429.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-site-score.png 1277w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you scroll down to the Basic SEO section, you&#8217;ll find the whole analysis and recommendations on what you need to improve.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"574\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo.png\" alt=\"Basic SEO analysis in All in One SEO \" class=\"wp-image-24654\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-600x472.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, from the above screenshot, it looks like this website is missing alt attributes in some images. Now that you know this, you can fix them and raise your SEO score. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The optimization process can&#8217;t get much easier than that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you think this was it? Far from it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO takes this a step further and is offering an Advanced SEO<strong> </strong>analysis as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"502\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo.png\" alt=\"Advanced SEO analysis in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24655\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-300x206.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-600x413.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p> This tool checks for advanced SEO factors like the use of canonical link tag, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-stop-search-engines-from-crawling-a-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">noindex header or meta tag</a>, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/www-vs-non-www-which-is-better-for-wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www and non-www URL redirects</a>, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/robots-txt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">robots.txt file</a>, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, AIOSEO already has one up on Yoast SEO with this great tool. With that said, let’s move on to looking at how both WordPress SEO plugins handle on-page optimization.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"on-page-optimization\">On-Page Optimization </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/infographics-template-seo-optimization.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"365\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/infographics-template-seo-optimization.jpg\" alt=\"Search engine optimization infographic by freepik\" class=\"wp-image-25551\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/infographics-template-seo-optimization.jpg 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/infographics-template-seo-optimization-300x150.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/infographics-template-seo-optimization-600x300.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Image Source: <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/premium-vector/infographics-template-seo-optimization_3698079.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">freepik</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>On-page optimization is an ongoing process, and each new post or page you add to your site will have its own SEO score.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This means you’ll be using your SEO plugin to optimize your content for search engines as you add it. For more details, check out our checklist on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">how to optimize your blog posts for SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>SEO Meta Box  </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Both plugins come with an SEO meta box to edit the SEO settings on a post by post basis. They automatically use your post or page’s title as SEO Title and excerpt as Meta Description, but you can also enter your own.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like we showed you earlier, AIOSEO makes this super easy with lots of different variables you can use to optimize your metadata, while Yoast SEO only has variables for the title, page, separator, and site title.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO meta box in Yoast SEO also looks a bit cluttered and feels outdated since it starts with the Focus keyphrase option that&#8217;s not really important for SEO anymore.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"764\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-title-and-meta-description.png\" alt=\"SEO title and meta description in Yoast SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24644\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-title-and-meta-description.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-title-and-meta-description-287x300.png 287w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-title-and-meta-description-600x628.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>In contrast to Yoast SEO, All in One SEO&#8217;s meta box begins with a Snippet Preview<strong> </strong>of your post or page’s SEO. This is very helpful so that users can see how their Post Title and Meta Description will look in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"565\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-general-post-title-and-description.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO general settings for post title and meta description \" class=\"wp-image-24637\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-general-post-title-and-description.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-general-post-title-and-description-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-general-post-title-and-description-600x464.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can write the Post Title and Meta Description manually or use the tags with different variables.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this reason, AIOSEO&#8217;s meta box is more logical. It starts with the most important element you should be optimizing and ends with less important factors like the Focus Keyphrase. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you still want to check your Focus Keyphrase, AIOSEO even gives you a score of how well your keyphrase is optimized and recommendations on how to improve it. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"356\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-focus-keyphrase-analysis.png\" alt=\"Focus keyphrase score and analysis in All in One SEO (AIOSEO) \" class=\"wp-image-24638\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-focus-keyphrase-analysis.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-focus-keyphrase-analysis-300x146.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-settings-focus-keyphrase-analysis-600x293.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While Yoast SEO briefly includes this feature in the content analysis tool, it doesn&#8217;t analyze it separately.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>On-Page Content Analysis </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The content analysis feature for both SEO plugins analyzes your content against SEO best practices. For instance, it checks the keyword density, readability, and the number of internal and external links. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also looks for keyphrase is used in the title, meta description, and first paragraph of your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, Yoast SEO was ahead of AIOSEO in regards to this feature. But AIOSEO later caught up with flying colors. We&#8217;ll show you exactly why next.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"693\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-analysis.png\" alt=\"SEO analysis in Yoast SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24645\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-analysis.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-analysis-300x285.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-seo-analysis-600x570.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While Yoast SEO provides a fairly detailed analysis of the page content and recommendations on how to improve your SEO, AIOSEO also does this, and more! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, AIOSEO even analyzes your Title and gives you immediate results on what you need to improve.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/title-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"241\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/title-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Title analysis tool in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25339\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/title-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/title-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo-300x99.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/title-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo-600x198.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It analyzes a few different factors in your title, including title length, if it includes a number, and if it&#8217;s using any <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/#write-a-captivating-blog-post-title\">power and sentiment words</a>. By optimizing your title, you can rest assured that it has all the elements that entice your visitors to click on it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Basic SEO, you&#8217;ll find a clear overview of the page analysis tool. As well as your overall post or page’s SEO score in the top right corner of your page. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"369\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-basic-seo.png\" alt=\"Basic SEO page analysis in All in One SEO (AIOSEO) \" class=\"wp-image-24639\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-basic-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-basic-seo-300x152.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-basic-seo-600x303.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Readability Analysis</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most important factors for SEO is readability. Blog posts that are easier to read often rank higher than posts that are difficult to read. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to the readability feature, both contenders are pretty similar. Although, Yoast SEO&#8217;s Readability analysis is more difficult to find since you have to navigate back to the main SEO menu. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"484\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-readability-score.png\" alt=\"Readability score in Yoast SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24646\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-readability-score.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-readability-score-300x199.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-readability-score-600x398.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s also squeezed in between the tabs for SEO, Schema, and Social.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While in AIOSEO, you can easily find the Readability tab to the right in Page Analysis. You can also find it by simply scrolling down below Additional Keyphrases inside the SEO meta box. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"551\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-readability.png\" alt=\"Readability analysis in All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-24643\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-readability.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-readability-300x226.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-page-analysis-readability-600x453.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So when it comes to on-page content analysis tools, AIOSEO is the best around. It&#8217;s much easier to navigate and will help you crush it in search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, we’ll move on to an important SEO factor, which is XML sitemaps. Let’s see if there are any major differences between our contenders with reference to this feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"xml-sitemaps\">XML Sitemaps</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you can rank on Google, your content needs to be indexed. If the search engines aren’t indexing your site, no amount of SEO can save you.&nbsp;That&#8217;s why XML sitemaps are important for SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both Yoast SEO and AIOSEO offer built-in XML sitemap functionality that’s enabled by default. But in contrast to Yoast SEO, AIOSEO also offers an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-an-rss-sitemap/?utm_source=WordPress&amp;utm_campaign=proplugin&amp;utm_medium=documentation&amp;utm_content=rssSitemaps\">RSS sitemap</a>, which is automatically submitted to search engines. It&#8217;s an important SEO tool because search engines check it much more frequently than an XML sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rss-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"390\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rss-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"RSS Sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25554\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rss-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rss-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rss-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x321.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An RSS sitemap includes only the latest changes to your site, which can then show up much faster in search results than the content of an XML sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, AIOSEO&#8217;s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing\">Pro version</a> allows you to customize your sitemap and also includes <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/video-seo-sitemaps/\">video sitemaps</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">Google News sitemaps</a>, etc.&nbsp;When it comes to Yoast SEO, these features are offered as addons. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Video Sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25556\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/sitemaps-video-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, please visit our post on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">how to create a sitemap in WordPress</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">how to submit your WordPress site to Google News</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, let’s move on to comparing additional SEO features for both plugins.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"additional-seo-tools-and-features\">Additional SEO Tools and Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO is a comprehensive process, which is why both of these plugins come with additional tools and features aside from just meta tags. Anyway, social media integration is one of these features that we&#8217;ll look at for both plugins next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Social Media Integration</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your social media is important because it can strengthen your brand. You&#8217;ll gain more visibility and can generate more leads for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO lets you add up to 11 social media profiles, whereas with Yoast SEO, you can only add 8 profiles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s show you how to add your social media profiles for both plugins, starting with AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do this in AIOSEO, you simply navigate to Social Networks<strong> </strong>in the All in One SEO menu.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"496\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-1.png\" alt=\"Social networks in All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-24648\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-1-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-1-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a window, where you can add all your Social Profiles.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"587\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles.png\" alt=\"Social profiles in All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-24649\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles-300x241.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles-600x482.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For Yoast SEO, you’ll find the social profiles in Social<strong> </strong>and the Accounts tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-profiles.png\" alt=\"Social accounts in Yoast SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24650\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-profiles.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-profiles-300x247.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-profiles-600x493.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, Yoast SEO has 3 fewer social media accounts to submit your links to.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And looking more closely, there are also differences in how you set your Facebook thumbnail and Twitter Cards for both plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can set your Facebook thumbnail and Twitter Cards from the Social Networks tab, but you can also do this from your individual posts or pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you’re editing your blog post or page, you can go directly to the Social<strong> </strong>tab in the AIOSEO Settings, and edit your Facebook thumbnail or Twitter Cards for each individual post and page. If you want to learn how to do this, you can check out our guides on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress/\">how to add Twitter Cards in WordPress</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress\">how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"726\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png\" alt=\"Set Facebook thumbnail in All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-24266\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png 726w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It gives you a beautiful preview of how your content will look when it’s shared on Facebook or Twitter. And you can also edit your title and description, as well as upload a featured image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Yoast SEO, the settings look more basic and the preview snippet doesn&#8217;t look as nice as in AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-facebook-settings.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-facebook-settings.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-24651\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-facebook-settings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-facebook-settings-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/yoast-seo-social-facebook-settings-600x384.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To summarize, both plugins offer similar social media integration. But AIOSEO gives you the option to tell Google about 3 more of your social media profiles. It also comes with a better social network window that’s easier to navigate and simply looks better.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But is that all additional SEO tools and features? Of course not!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s also take a look at more advanced SEO tools for both contenders.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Advanced SEO Tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Advanced SEO tools help you further optimize your site for search engines without having to install any additional plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, both SEO plugins offer key features like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Built-in robots.txt and .htaccess editor</li><li>XML Sitemaps</li><li>Import and export SEO data</li><li>Breadcrumb navigation</li><li>Canonical links</li><li>404 not found page redirect manager</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from these tools, AIOSEO also offers <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/access-controls/\">User Access Control</a>, which is an awesome tool. It allows you to manage access to important SEO features without handing over control of your website. Please check out the video if you want a sneak peek at how it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"All in One SEO&#039;s SEO Manager Role\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NjTyy7qCc44?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can probably understand why this is important when running a big business with many employees that all have different roles within the company. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, AIOSEO also comes with advanced <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/woocommerce-seo/\">eCommerce SEO</a> support for WooCommerce to optimize product pages, product categories, and more. As well as <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/local-seo/\">Local SEO</a> to help you rank on Google maps, and easily submit your business name, logo, address, and phone number to search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For Yoast SEO, you have to buy these features as extra functionalities, meaning separate plugins. Or you&#8217;d have to buy the full Yoast SEO package including all SEO plugins, which is quite expensive. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"paid-plans-and-pricing\">Paid Plans and Pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As your site grows, you’ll want to improve your SEO so that you can climb the rankings on Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the free versions come with minimal features, premium versions give you more control over your website&#8217;s SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, deciding on a plan can be confusing. We’ll try to break down the important facts about these 2 plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Free Plans for 1 Single Website</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you’re just starting out, you’ll want to start with the free version of your SEO plugin to try it out. Both <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-seo-pack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AIOSEO</a> and  <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Yoast SEO</a> offer a free version.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s free version has over 2+ million active installations and 1142 five star ratings. In other words, over 2 million smart website owners use AIOSEO to properly set up WordPress SEO, so their websites can rank higher in search engines. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"520\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1.png\" alt=\"The best WordPress SEO plugin All in One SEO \" class=\"wp-image-25264\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1-300x214.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1-600x427.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Paid Plans for Several Websites</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you feel you want to use more advanced SEO tools on a single site, you can start with AIOSEO&#8217;s Basic plan for as little as $49 per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you want to take your SEO efforts to the next level, you should consider buying the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Plus</a> version for $99.50 per year (up to 3 sites) or the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro</a> version for $199.50 per year (up to 10 sites). </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"481\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-pricing.png\" alt=\"Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO - pricing for AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24663\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-pricing.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-pricing-300x198.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-pricing-600x395.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Elite</a> version is for business owners with up to 100 sites. And the Pro and Elite versions also offer 1 year of professional priority support.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yoast SEO is priced higher than AIOSEO for all its versions. Pricing for a <a href=\"https://yoast.com/wordpress/plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">single site license</a> starts at $89 per year and moves up to $169 per year (for up to 5 sites). And yet, these plans don&#8217;t even include many of the advanced SEO tools that All in One SEO offers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead, you have to buy the different SEO features separately, which gets quite expensive since they are $89 per year each.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to include all features, the price increases to $329 per year (for up to 20 sites). </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did we say that you can get up to 100 websites (all features included) for only $299.50 with AIOSEO’s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Elite</a> version?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That pretty much summarizes which of the SEO plugins should be your one and only choice!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, to give you that extra sense of security, AIOSEO also offers a 14-day no-risk money back guarantee. So if your plan isn’t a good fit, you can get your money back. You don’t even need to give a reason for the refund.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-no-risk-money-back-guarantee.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"254\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-no-risk-money-back-guarantee.png\" alt=\"100% No-Risk Money Back Guarantee for All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25603\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-no-risk-money-back-guarantee.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-no-risk-money-back-guarantee-300x104.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-no-risk-money-back-guarantee-600x209.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, let’s take a look at the support you’ll get from the Premium and Pro versions of both SEO plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-support\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO Support</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Even though both plugins are fairly easy to use and come with extensive free documentation and video tutorials, your free support options are limited. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But we didn&#8217;t say none!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Support for Free Versions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Both SEO plugins offer support for free users through <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/all-in-one-seo-pack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WordPress forums</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As of writing this Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO post:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>AIOSEO has resolved 201 out of 279 support threads (72%)</li><li>Yoast SEO has resolved 563 out of 612 support threads (91%)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The response time is 1-3 working days for both plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Support for Paid Versions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you pay for either of these plugins, you can access ticket support as well. Within 1 day, you can expect a response to the support tickets from both Yoast SEO and AIOSEO support teams. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, AIOSEO gives you extensive documentation on how to configure all different SEO tools in their <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/\">Docs tab</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"424\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-documentation-and-tutorials.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO documentation and tutorials\" class=\"wp-image-25593\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-documentation-and-tutorials.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-documentation-and-tutorials-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-documentation-and-tutorials-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don&#8217;t find what you&#8217;re looking for, you can also search for it with the search tool. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having all of these different support options makes it easy to get help whenever you need it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-which-is-best\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO: Which Is Best?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"706\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-24673\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress-300x290.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress-600x580.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Image Source: <a href=\"https://www.lipperhey.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Lipperhey</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO and Yoast SEO are both great plugins. They are developed with the same goal – to make SEO tasks easy and straightforward for WordPress websites. And they are both doing that exceptionally well!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, as you&#8217;ve probably understood by now, AIOSEO has passed Yoast SEO with flying colors and is absolutely the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market. For instance, it offers more advanced SEO tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/access-controls/\">user access control</a>, the option to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">customize your sitemaps</a>, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget, the awesome on-page <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/seo-audit-checklist/\">SEO audit checklist tool</a>. As well as the option to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">analyze your competitors’ SEO</a>. These are great tools to get ahead of your competitors and gain an edge. And totally unique for All in One SEO!</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Undeniably, AIOSEO also comes in a neater, tidier, and altogether more user-friendly packaging. And when it comes to setting up SEO for individual posts and pages, AIOSEO makes this easier too.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, AIOSEO is a lot cheaper than Yoast SEO. Besides, it even allows you to add up to 100 websites in contrast to only 20 sites for Yoast SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And did we tell you that if you&#8217;re running a news site, you can automatically <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">submit it to Google News</a>? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can go on and on with how great AIOSEO is, but to try and summarize this post, we&#8217;ll put it like this: Improving your SEO efforts in all areas can&#8217;t get much easier. So if you’re looking for the best SEO plugin on the market, get <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this comparison of Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO helped you find the best WordPress SEO plugin for your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a> to learn how to boost rankings even more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you, as always, for supporting the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>!</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-which-is-the-best-seo-plugin/\">Yoast SEO vs All in One SEO: Which Is the Best SEO Plugin?</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://aioseo.com/yoast-seo-vs-all-in-one-seo-which-is-the-best-seo-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:158:\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/?utm_source=rss&utm