ef=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\">How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42288:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add schema markup to your WordPress website without a plugin?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup can drastically increase CTR (Click Through Rate) to your site. And proof of that is Jobrapido that added a Job Posting schema markup to their site and got a <a href=\"https://econsultancy.com/case-studies-structured-data-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">270%</a> increase in new user registrations from their organic traffic.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to add schema markup to WordPress without a plugin, as well as give you a better and easier option to do this.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please feel free to use the quick links below to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#is-it-best-to-add-schema-with-or-without-a-plugin\">Is It Best to Add Schema With or Without a Plugin?</a></li><li><a href=\"#benefits-of-adding-schema-markup\">Benefits of Adding Schema Markup</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin\">Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#an-easier-way-to-add-schema-markup-to-wordpress\">An Easier Way to Add Schema Markup to WordPress</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>But first, let’s start by answering the question whether it’s best to add schema with or without a plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"is-it-best-to-add-schema-with-or-without-a-plugin\">Is It Best to Add Schema With or Without a Plugin?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"520\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1.png\" alt=\"The best WordPress SEO plugin, All in One SEO \" class=\"wp-image-25264\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1-300x214.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/all-in-one-seo-wordpress-plugin-1-600x427.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plugins add new functionality to your WordPress site without having to use code. And yet, many users believe that the fewer plugins they use on their sites the better, but that’s not always true.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s true that badly coded plugins could add bloat and slow down your site. But a well-made, lightweight plugin can simplify things and save you a lot of time, without any ill effects.&nbsp;If that didn’t convince you, check out WPBeginner’s post on <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-wordpress-plugins-affect-your-sites-load-time/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how plugins affect your site’s speed</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we get into things, let’s take a look at why adding schema markup without a plugin may not be the best choice for your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>It’s Difficult and Time Consuming </strong>– not using an SEO plugin to create schema is difficult and takes a lot of extra time. You also need to know how to use PHP code.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>You Can’t Update Your Theme&nbsp; </strong>– it&#8217;s never a good idea to edit theme files directly. When the theme updates, all your edits will be gone.</li><li><strong>You Can’t Switch WordPress Theme</strong> – you can’t change your WordPress theme since your custom code will only work if you’re using that particular theme.</li><li><strong>You’ll Miss Out on Powerful Features</strong> – with a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">AIOSEO</a>, you can easily include advanced markups such as Articles, Breadcrumbs, and Sitelinks Search Box. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s take a closer look at the benefits of schema markups and how they can improve your CTR (Click Through Rate).</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"benefits-of-adding-schema-markup\">Benefits of Adding Schema Markup </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The benefits of adding schema markup to your WordPress site are many. For instance, you’ve probably seen those nice looking search results with star ratings and prices like this example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"Example of a rich snippet in Google\" class=\"wp-image-25079\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Google-rich-snippet-example-600x334.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These are called <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/rich-snippets-schema/\">rich snippets</a>, and you get them by adding schema markup to your web pages. They give direct information to users about what a page is about and make it look better in search. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With other words, schema markups are used by all big search engines like Google, Bing, Yahoo, and Yandex to show additional information in their search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, rich snippets increase the CTR to your site since they make your content look more visually appealing when displayed in search engines. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And more clicks will eventually lead to higher rankings as well.&nbsp;It’s a great way of boosting your SEO and get more organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rich-snippet-infographic.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"574\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rich-snippet-infographic.png\" alt=\"Rich snippet infographic\" class=\"wp-image-25239\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rich-snippet-infographic.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rich-snippet-infographic-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/rich-snippet-infographic-600x472.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Image Source: <a href=\"https://brandongaille.com/15-rich-snippets-markup-examples-for-breadcrumbs-recipes-and-products/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Brandon Gaille</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Difference Between Rich Snippets and Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wait a second, we’re talking about rich snippets and schema markup like they’re the same?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not quite! Let’s explain the difference between the two. Simply put, while rich snippets are for humans, schema markups are for search engine bots.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup is the code that tells Google what your content is about. And rich snippets are what Google displays in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also referred to as structured data since it uses a code language accepted by major search engines.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add schema markup to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Articles</li><li>Events</li><li>Reviews</li><li>Recipes</li><li>Books</li><li>Products</li><li>FAQs&nbsp;</li><li>And much more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyhow, there are two ways to add schema markup to your site. The best and easiest method is by using the best and most powerful SEO plugin in the market, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>. We’ll show you how easy this is in section: <a href=\"#an-easier-way-to-add-schema-markup-to-wordpress\">an easier way to add schema markup to WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The second way is to add it manually without a plugin, and that’s what we’re going to show you how to do next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin\">Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-org-homepage.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-org-homepage.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-25116\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-org-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-org-homepage-300x94.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-org-homepage-600x187.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, you can visit <a href=\"https://schema.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Schema.org</a> to find the markup you want to add to your content. We’ll show you how to add the Article markup to your WordPress site. But you can find all schema markups that are supported by search engines on Schema.org.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These markups are using 3 different code languages:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Microdata</li><li>RDFa</li><li>JSON LD</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re going to use JSON–LD since Google likes it better and it doesn’t break your site as easily as other markups can do.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let’s take a look at how to add <strong>Article markup</strong> on your post or page in WordPress using the block editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>WordPress Block Editor</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, simply log in to your <strong>WordPress Dashboard </strong>and navigate to any <strong>Post</strong> or <strong>Page</strong> you want to add schema to.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/wordpress-dashboard-posts.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"291\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/wordpress-dashboard-posts.png\" alt=\"WordPress dashboard posts\" class=\"wp-image-25080\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/wordpress-dashboard-posts.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/wordpress-dashboard-posts-300x120.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/wordpress-dashboard-posts-600x239.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to make sure that <strong>Custom Fields</strong> are checked in the <strong>Options</strong> tab. Click on the 3 dots in the top right corner, and it will open a new view. Then, scroll down to Options in the Tools section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/options-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"745\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/options-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Options in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-25081\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/options-in-wordpress-block-editor.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/options-in-wordpress-block-editor-284x300.png 284w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/options-in-wordpress-block-editor-600x633.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a new window with all panel options. Here you need to check the <strong>Customs Fields</strong> box.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-panels-custom-fileds-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"687\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-panels-custom-fileds-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Customs fields in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-25082\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-panels-custom-fileds-in-wordpress-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-panels-custom-fileds-in-wordpress-block-editor-300x282.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/advanced-panels-custom-fileds-in-wordpress-block-editor-600x565.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you simply return to the block editor and scroll down in your post or page to the bottom, where you can see the Custom Fields settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enter-new-custom-field-in-block-editor.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"218\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enter-new-custom-field-in-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Enter new custom field in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-25084\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enter-new-custom-field-in-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enter-new-custom-field-in-block-editor-300x90.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enter-new-custom-field-in-block-editor-600x179.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>Add New Custom Field,</strong> you click on the <strong>Enter new</strong> tab.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to <strong>Name</strong> your schema markup. In this example, we’ve named it <strong>Article Schema</strong> since we’ll add a markup for article.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-schema-name-and-value-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"160\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-schema-name-and-value-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Add schema name and value in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-25085\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-schema-name-and-value-in-wordpress-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-schema-name-and-value-in-wordpress-block-editor-300x66.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-schema-name-and-value-in-wordpress-block-editor-600x132.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve named your markup, you’ll need to copy the code snippet below and paste it in the <strong>Value</strong> section<strong>. </strong>If you haven’t written code before but want to use a different markup, you can use the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/webmasters/markup-helper/u/0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Structured Data Markup Helper</a> or <a href=\"https://schemagenerator.net/#:~:text=%20How%20to%20Generate%20Schema%20Markup%20using%20JSON-LD,4%3A%20.%20Optional-%20Validate%20generated%20sc...%20More%20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Schema Markup Generators</a>. They will generate the code for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;script type=\"application/ld+json\"&gt;\n    {\n      \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n      \"@type\": \"NewsArticle\",\n      \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\n        \"@type\": \"WebPage\",\n        \"@id\": \"https://google.com/article\"\n      },\n      \"headline\": \"Article headline\",\n      \"image\": &#91;\n        \"https://example.com/photos/1x1/photo.jpg\",\n        \"https://example.com/photos/4x3/photo.jpg\",\n        \"https://example.com/photos/16x9/photo.jpg\"\n       ],\n      \"datePublished\": \"2015-02-05T08:00:00+08:00\",\n      \"dateModified\": \"2015-02-05T09:20:00+08:00\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Person\",\n        \"name\": \"John Doe\"\n      },\n       \"publisher\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Google\",\n        \"logo\": {\n          \"@type\": \"ImageObject\",\n          \"url\": \"https://google.com/logo.jpg\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    &lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>After you’ve added the code in Value, click on the <strong>Add Custom Field</strong> button. Then, scroll up to the top of the page and click on <strong>Update</strong> to save your changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-custom-field-in-block-editor-1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"160\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-custom-field-in-block-editor-1.png\" alt=\"Add custom field in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-25088\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-custom-field-in-block-editor-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-custom-field-in-block-editor-1-300x66.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-custom-field-in-block-editor-1-600x132.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’re almost finished.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The last step is to copy this code snippet and add it to your<strong> header.php</strong> file:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;?php\n$schema = get_post_meta(get_the_ID(), \'schema\', true);\nif(!empty($schema)) {\n    echo $schema;\n}\n?&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll show you how to do that next.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>We need to warn you that one single mistake when editing theme files can bring your whole website down and cause the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-fix-the-wordpress-white-screen-of-death/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">white screen of death</a>. Always make sure to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/7-best-wordpress-backup-plugins-compared-pros-and-cons/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">backup</a> your site before you start. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Safely Add Custom Code to Your Header.php File </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The best and safest option is always to use a plugin to add custom code and functionality to your site. And we strongly recommend using the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Insert Headers and Footers</a> WordPress plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So before we show you how to directly edit the theme files, we&#8217;ll show you how easy it is to add your code snippet to the header.php file using the Insert Headers and Footers plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After installing and activating the plugin, you simply navigate to your <strong>WordPress Dashboard</strong> and click on <strong>Insert Headers and Footers</strong> in the <strong>Settings</strong> menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/insert-headers-and-footers-wordpress-plugin.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"466\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/insert-headers-and-footers-wordpress-plugin.png\" alt=\"Insert Headers and Footers WordPress plugin\" class=\"wp-image-25245\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/insert-headers-and-footers-wordpress-plugin.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/insert-headers-and-footers-wordpress-plugin-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/insert-headers-and-footers-wordpress-plugin-600x383.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you&#8217;ll see different windows for adding your code to the Header, Body, and Footer of your site. Make sure to add your code snippet in the <strong>Scripts in Header </strong>window.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/scripts-in-header-in-insert-headers-and-footers.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"527\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/scripts-in-header-in-insert-headers-and-footers.png\" alt=\"Add scripts in header - Insert Headers and Footers WordPress plugin\" class=\"wp-image-25246\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/scripts-in-header-in-insert-headers-and-footers.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/scripts-in-header-in-insert-headers-and-footers-300x217.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/scripts-in-header-in-insert-headers-and-footers-600x433.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the <strong>Save</strong> button, and that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can&#8217;t get much easier than that! Best of all, it&#8217;s much safer than editing the theme files directly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Custom Code Directly in Your Theme Files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let&#8217;s move on to how to add the code snippet directly in the theme editor and header.php file.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply go to <strong>Appearance » Theme Editor</strong> and click on&nbsp;the <strong>header.php</strong> file in <strong>Theme Files</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/appearance-theme-editor-header-php.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"318\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/appearance-theme-editor-header-php.png\" alt=\"WordPress theme editor header.php\" class=\"wp-image-25252\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/appearance-theme-editor-header-php.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/appearance-theme-editor-header-php-300x131.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/appearance-theme-editor-header-php-600x261.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a new window, where you can edit the file.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, paste in the schema code in the file editor just before the <strong>&lt;/head&gt;</strong> tag.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/theme-editor-header-php.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"396\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/theme-editor-header-php.png\" alt=\"WordPress theme editor header.php\" class=\"wp-image-25254\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/theme-editor-header-php.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/theme-editor-header-php-300x163.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/theme-editor-header-php-600x325.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After you’ve added the code snippet, click on the <strong>Update File</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, reload your page and you’ll see the schema markup just before the closing tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have now successfully added schema to WordPress without a plugin, and can test your URL to check if there are any errors using <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool/u/0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google’s Structured Data Testing Tool</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to add schema without a plugin, we&#8217;ll show you a better and easier way to add schema markup to your WordPress website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"an-easier-way-to-add-schema-markup-to-wordpress\">An Easier Way to Add Schema Markup to WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO The Best WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-23910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s a better and easier way to add schema markup to your site using the most powerful WordPress SEO plugin, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to mention, many other advanced <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\">SEO tools</a> that will improve your SEO and increase rankings in search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some of these powerful SEO tools:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>SEO Custom User Roles </strong>— allow you to manage access to important SEO features without handing over control of your website.</li><li><strong>SEO Audit Checklist</strong> —<strong> </strong>analyze your entire WordPress site to detect critical errors and get actionable insights to boost your SEO and get more traffic.</li><li><strong>Smart XML Sitemaps </strong>— automatically generate a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">WordPress XML sitemap</a> and notify all search engines of any updates.</li><li><strong>Google News Sitemap</strong> — get higher rankings and unlock more traffic by submitting your latest news articles to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">Google News</a>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know a few of AIOSEO’s advanced SEO tools, let’s take a look at what you can add schema to.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add schema to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Articles</li><li>Breadcrumbs</li><li>Sitelinks Search Boxes</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Breadcrumb and Sitelinks Search Box schema markups are sent automatically to search engines. As well as <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-corporate-contacts-in-schema-markup/\">Corporate Contacts</a> and Organization Logos that are sent to <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/guides/enhance-site\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google’s Knowledge Graph</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started adding schema, you first need to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">install and activate AIOSEO</a> on your WordPress website. If you haven’t installed a plugin before, you can check out WPBeginner’s guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve installed AIOSEO, we&#8217;ll show you how to set if you&#8217;re a person or organization so that you can tell Google about your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Person or Organization</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, click on <strong>Search Appearance</strong>. Next, go to the <strong>Global Settings</strong> tab and scroll down to the <strong>Schema Markup</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - search appearance in All in One SEO menu\" class=\"wp-image-25089\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x277.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is choose whether your site represents a <strong>Person </strong>or<strong> Organization</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-or-organization-in-schema-markup-settings.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"159\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-or-organization-in-schema-markup-settings.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - person or organization \" class=\"wp-image-25090\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-or-organization-in-schema-markup-settings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-or-organization-in-schema-markup-settings-300x65.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-or-organization-in-schema-markup-settings-600x131.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on what you choose, you’ll see fields where you need to enter your information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For <strong>Organization</strong>, you need to enter the following information:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/organization-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/organization-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress -  organization \" class=\"wp-image-25091\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/organization-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/organization-settings-in-schema-markup-settings-300x189.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/organization-settings-in-schema-markup-settings-600x379.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>In the <strong>Name</strong> field –&nbsp; enter the name of your organization or business</li><li>In the <strong>Phone Number</strong> field – enter the phone number for your business you’d like listed on search engines</li><li>In the <strong>Contact Type</strong> field – select what type that best describes the <strong>Phone Number</strong> you entered</li><li>In the <strong>Logo</strong> field – upload the logo for your organization or business</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The image has to be a minimum size of 112px x 112px and in jpg, png, or gif format. Also, if you don’t upload a logo, AIOSEO will use the logo that you added to your theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a <strong>Personal </strong>site, you need to enter this information:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"361\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - person\" class=\"wp-image-25092\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-settings-in-schema-markup-settings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-settings-in-schema-markup-settings-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/person-settings-in-schema-markup-settings-600x297.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>In the <strong>Choose a Person</strong> field – choose the primary owner for your site from the list of users. Only users with the role of Author, Editor, or Administrator will be listed here</li><li>You can also select the <strong>Manually Enter Person</strong> option from the drop down and then complete the <strong>Name</strong> and <strong>Logo</strong> fields</li><li>In the <strong>Name</strong> field – enter the name of the primary owner for your site</li><li>In the <strong>Logo</strong> field – upload an image of the primary owner (the same size requirements as for organization)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s move on to enabling sitelinks search box for your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Sitelinks Search Box</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A sitelinks search box is a quick way for people to search your site directly from the search results on Google. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of a sitelinks search box for Pinterest:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-of-sitelinks-search-box-in-google.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-of-sitelinks-search-box-in-google.png\" alt=\"Example of sitelinks search box for Pinterest\" class=\"wp-image-25093\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-of-sitelinks-search-box-in-google.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-of-sitelinks-search-box-in-google-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/example-of-sitelinks-search-box-in-google-600x325.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Image Source: <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/data-types/sitelinks-searchbox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Central</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>Enable Sitelinks Search Box</strong>, make sure that the button is set to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitelinks-search-box-setting.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"105\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitelinks-search-box-setting.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - enable sitelinks search box\" class=\"wp-image-25094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitelinks-search-box-setting.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitelinks-search-box-setting-300x43.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-sitelinks-search-box-setting-600x86.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AlOSEO will then send the code for the sitelinks search box so that Google can show it in search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’ve completed the main schema markup settings, we’ll move on to adding schema to your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Adding Schema to Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, you need to navigate to the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu and click on <strong>Search Appearance</strong>. The next step is to click on the <strong>Content Types</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-content-types-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-content-types-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - search appearance content types in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25095\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-content-types-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-content-types-in-all-in-one-seo-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-content-types-in-all-in-one-seo-600x277.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you’ll see sections for each of the types of content on your site such as posts, pages, and products.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll add<strong> </strong>schema to<strong> Post </strong>types for your site. While in Posts, click on the <strong>Schema Markup</strong> to set schema for your <strong>Schema Type </strong>and <strong>Article Type</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-content-types.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"280\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-content-types.png\" alt=\"Setting schema markup for posts in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25096\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-content-types.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-content-types-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-content-types-600x230.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you have <strong>Article </strong>as Schema Type. It&#8217;s the best option for blog posts and news articles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below Schema Type, you’ll see a setting for <strong>Article Type</strong>. It’s set to <strong>Blog Post</strong> by default, but you can choose what fits your content the best.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can repeat these steps for pages and products too.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Schema to Your Taxonomies</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to add schema to your content, we’ll move on to taxonomies.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, click on <strong>Search Appearance</strong> and then the <strong>Taxonomies</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-taxonomies-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-taxonomies-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - search appearance taxonomies in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25097\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-taxonomies-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-taxonomies-in-all-in-one-seo-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/search-appearance-menu-taxonomies-in-all-in-one-seo-600x277.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like in the schema settings for posts, you’ll see sections for each of the taxonomies for the content on your site such as categories, tags, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply, click on the <strong>Schema Markup</strong> tab in each section to configure Schema for that taxonomy. In this example, we’ll show you how to add schema to <strong>Categories</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-taxonomies.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"288\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-taxonomies.png\" alt=\"Setting schema markup for categories in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25098\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-taxonomies.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-taxonomies-300x118.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-taxonomies-600x237.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can choose your <strong>Schema Type</strong> and <strong>Article Type, </strong>just like you did for<strong> </strong>posts. Then, repeat this process for your other taxonomies.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The last step is to set schema type for your individual content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Schema to Your Individual Posts and Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add schema markup directly in the editor for your blog post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> at the bottom of your post or page, and click on the <strong>Schema</strong> tab. This will open a new window, where you can select <strong>Schema Type</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-individual-pages.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"355\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-individual-pages.png\" alt=\"Setting schema markup for individual posts and pages in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-25099\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-individual-pages.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-individual-pages-300x146.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-markup-settings-for-individual-pages-600x292.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the drop-down to set the Schema Type for your post or page. If you choose the <strong>Default (Set in Search Appearance) </strong>option, AIOSEO will use your prior settings in Search Appearance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step is to choose <strong>Article Type</strong> for your content. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-type-settings-on-individual-content.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"74\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-type-settings-on-individual-content.png\" alt=\"Add schema markup to WordPress - article type\" class=\"wp-image-25102\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-type-settings-on-individual-content.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-type-settings-on-individual-content-300x30.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/schema-type-settings-on-individual-content-600x61.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, <strong>Blog Post</strong> is set as the default option, but you can choose whichever you feel best fits your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s all!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now set schema markup on individual posts or pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this blog post helped you learn how to add schema markup to your WordPress website without a plugin. And also showed you a better and easier way to add schema markup to your site without having to use PHP code.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><span class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</span></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>One last thing before you go!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to learn how to optimize your blog post for SEO like a pro, make sure to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for AIOSEO’s new features and improvements.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, thanks for supporting <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">the best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\">How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:180:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 14 Jan 2021 13:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"add site to google search console\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"google search console\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"google search console wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"how to add google search console to wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"how to submit website to google\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=24887\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:521:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website? In this post, we’ll show you how to add Google Search Console to your site so that you can monitor its presence in Google search results, as well as drive more traffic, boost conversations, and grow your website.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17222:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website? One of the most important steps in optimizing your WordPress site for SEO is adding it to Google Search Console.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that the average person searches for something online <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">3-4 times a day</a>? It&#8217;s therefore important to make sure Google sees your website and shows it in search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the first step to driving traffic to your site, boosting conversions, and growing your business. After all, if Google doesn’t know your site exists, no one else will either.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website so that you can monitor your site’s presence in Google search results and improve your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please feel free to use these quick links to jump straight to the sections you want:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-google-search-console\">What Is Google Search Console?</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a></li><li><a href=\"#easily-verify-your-wordpress-site-using-asioseo\">Easily Verify Your WordPress Site Using AIOSEO</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start with explaining what Google Search Console is and why it&#8217;s a helpful tool for all website owners.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"what-is-google-search-console\"><strong>What Is Google Search Console?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"614\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png\" alt=\"How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website\" class=\"wp-image-25056\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage-300x252.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage-600x505.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Search Console, formerly known as “Google Webmaster Tools,” is a free service available to all website owners.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It shows you how Google indexes and adds your website to Google search results so that you can make sure the right people are seeing your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Google Search Console, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Confirm that Google can locate and crawl your WordPress site</li><li>Submit new content for indexing, and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">add a sitemap</a></li><li>Analyze your site&#8217;s impressions, clicks, and position on Google</li><li>See which search queries (search terms) cause your site to appear in search results</li><li>Delete or <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-hide-a-wordpress-page-from-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">hide content from Google</a> so it doesn’t appear in search results</li><li>Find and fix common malware and spam issues</li><li>See which other sites are linking to your site</li><li>Test if your mobile site is driving traffic to your site</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, Google Search Console is a helpful tool that gives you information about your site and the people visiting it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, are you serious about growing your website? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then you need to add it to Google Search Console&nbsp;from day one!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being the case, let’s take a look at how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Site\" class=\"wp-image-24893\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress-600x283.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, head over to <a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Console</a> and click on the <strong>Start Now</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, sign in with your Google / Gmail account.&nbsp;If you don’t have one yet, you can create an account <a href=\"https://support.google.com/mail/answer/56256?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s easy and will only take you a couple of minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve created your Google / Gmail account and logged in, you’ll see a welcome page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"Welcome to Google Search Console page\" class=\"wp-image-24894\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console-300x245.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console-600x490.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the right side of the page, you’ll see a box called <strong>URL prefix</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on this box and enter the full URL for your website and then click the <strong>Continue </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"620\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - enter URL prefix\" class=\"wp-image-24895\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console-300x263.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console-600x527.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The URL you enter must exactly match the URL for your site. This includes https://&nbsp;and www, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you&#8217;ve clicked continue, it will take you to a new <strong>Verify ownership</strong> window. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re going to use the HTML tag to verify your WordPress website with Google.&nbsp;With that said, simply scroll down to <strong>Other verification</strong> methods, and click on the <strong>HTML tag </strong>option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"716\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - HTML tag\" class=\"wp-image-24896\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console-300x294.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console-600x588.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a new window with the meta tag that you need to add to your WordPress site’s homepage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"523\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - copy HTML tag\" class=\"wp-image-24897\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console-300x215.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console-600x430.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you need to click on the<strong> Copy</strong> button to copy the HTML tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, you can now open a new browser window and log into your WordPress site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the next step, we&#8217;re going to show you how to easily verify your WordPress site with Google Search Console using the best SEO plugin in the market, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"easily-verify-your-wordpress-site-using-asioseo\">Easily Verify Your WordPress Site Using AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO The Best WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-23910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Why should you use AIOSEO to verify your site with Google Search Console, you may ask?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many reasons why you should use AIOSEO to verify your site, as well as for other SEO practices. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And here are a few:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>You Will Lose All Your Hard Work</strong> – It&#8217;s never a good idea to edit theme files directly. When the theme updates, all your edits will be gone.</li><li><strong>You’ll Miss Out on Powerful Features</strong> – with AIOSEO, you can easily include advanced SEO features that will improve rankings and drive more traffic to your site. For example, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">XML sitemap</a>, schema markup, social media integration, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">SEO audit and competitor analysis</a>, WooCommerce SEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/\">nofollow links</a>, and so much more. </li><li><strong>Best of All, It&#8217;s Much Easier</strong> – an SEO plugin makes your work so much easier. You don&#8217;t have to know code, and most features are enabled by default, so you only have to install the plugin and it&#8217;s all set! </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know why you should use AIOSEO, let&#8217;s take a look at how to easily verify your site with Google Search Console.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Verification Process</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, you first need to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">install and activate AIOSEO</a> on your WordPress website. If you haven’t installed a plugin before, you can check out Beginner’s guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you click on <strong>General Settings</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, and then the <strong>Webmaster Tools</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/webmaster-verification-screen-in-all-in-one-seo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"375\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/webmaster-verification-screen-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"General settings webmaster tools in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24898\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/webmaster-verification-screen-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/webmaster-verification-screen-in-all-in-one-seo-300x154.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/webmaster-verification-screen-in-all-in-one-seo-600x308.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click on the <strong>Google Search Console</strong> block and paste the code you copied from Google into the <strong>Google Verification Code</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-using-aioseo.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"226\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-using-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Google Search Console verification in All in One SEO \" class=\"wp-image-24899\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-using-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-using-aioseo-300x93.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-using-aioseo-600x186.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step is to go back to Google Search Console in your other browser window and click on the <strong>Verify</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/qLuBZboi2G8uMFt_2wlkrQNaQ1KsLFmIjIcPCK_Q-RrEVM95Z5YZtHunMv4xL8eCm_QNI0TvrAv-VrUcX2MQJmhLM54Ew8UUqkOKhOe5WYKEDkvsCf8uTcJji7LAUq_bjvMqId1U\" alt=\"Verify ownership in Google Search Console \"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Search Console will now look for the HTML tag in your site’s code and will show you an <strong>Ownership verified</strong> message.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"323\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success.png\" alt=\"Ownership verified in Google Search Console\" class=\"wp-image-24900\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success-300x137.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success-704x323.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-verified-success-600x275.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you don’t see this message, then you need to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-clear-your-cache-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">clear your WordPress cache</a>. It will ensure that Google can fetch the latest version of your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And there you have it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now successfully added Google Search Console to your WordPress website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But are you really going to stop there?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’re up and running with Google Search Console, you should also add an XML Sitemap to help Google crawl your site easier. If you want to learn how to easily do this, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">how to create a sitemap in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re looking for great ways to improve your overall SEO to drive even more traffic to your site, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we go, we want to let you know that you can integrate Google Analytics with the help of <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-configure-your-wordpress-website-with-google-search-console/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MonsterInsights</a> to track your traffic even better. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, thanks for supporting <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">the best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">Click here to get started with AIOSEO today!</a></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"How to Fix Wrong Facebook Thumbnail in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:160:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 07 Jan 2021 13:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"facebook debugger\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"facebook thumbnail wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"facebook thumbnails not showing up when sharing link\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"how to fix wrong facebook thumbnail\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"wrong facebook thumbnail\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=24260\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:447:\"<p>Is the wrong Facebook thumbnail displayed when you share your articles or blog posts? In this post, we’ll show you how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress. We\'ll also cover how to use Facebook\'s debug tool to clear the cache.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/\">How to Fix Wrong Facebook Thumbnail in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20940:\"<p>Is the wrong Facebook thumbnail displayed when you share your articles or blog posts?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a problem you should solve quickly since Facebook thumbnails capture people’s interest and make them more likely to click on and share your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing how to make the right thumbnail show up isn’t always clear, but don’t worry, because we’re here to help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#facebook-thumbnails-not-showing-when-sharing-link\">Facebook Thumbnails Not Showing When Sharing Link</a></li><li><a href=\"#fixing-the-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-the-easy-way\">Fixing the Wrong Facebook Thumbnail (The Easy Way)</a></li><li><a href=\"#using-facebook-debug-tool-to-clear-the-cache\">Using Facebook Debug Tool to Clear the Cache</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start by taking a look at why Facebook thumbnails are important, and why they sometimes aren’t showing up when you’re sharing a link.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"facebook-thumbnails-not-showing-when-sharing-link\">Facebook Thumbnails Not Showing When Sharing Link</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"638\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-forum-facebook-engagement-infographic-1.png\" alt=\"Facebook engagement infographic by Ogilvy\" class=\"wp-image-24546\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-forum-facebook-engagement-infographic-1.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-forum-facebook-engagement-infographic-1-300x271.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/open-forum-facebook-engagement-infographic-1-600x542.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Image Source:  <a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/78390849735500475/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ogilvy Pinterest</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Facebook thumbnails are important to increase engagements and get referral traffic to your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Posts with images get 39% more clicks and shares on Facebook. This means that more people are likely to click through to your site or share your content on Facebook. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s therefore important to make sure your Facebook thumbnails are working properly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But before you can fix the problem, you need to understand why it occurs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, there are a few reasons why Facebook thumbnails or featured images aren’t showing up when sharing a link.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Reasons Why Facebook Thumbnails Aren&#8217;t Showing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First of all, if you&#8217;re not setting which Facebook thumbnail you want to use, Facebook usually “guesses” the image. It&#8217;s doing so by using Open Graph or og:Image tags. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don’t know about Open Graph meta tags, they are snippets of code that control how URLs are displayed when shared on social media.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Second of all, the most common reason why Facebook thumbnails aren’t showing is having multiple images set in the og:Image tag. Then Facebook often chooses the biggest image. Other reasons might be <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/best-wordpress-caching-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">caching plugins</a> or <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-wordpress-cdn-services/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">CDN conflicts</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress/\">one of our posts</a> looks like after choosing which thumbnail that’s used when it&#8217;s shared on Facebook:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example.png\" alt=\"Example of Facebook thumbnail for AIOSEO when you content is shared on Facebook\" class=\"wp-image-24265\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example-300x163.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example-600x326.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a> makes this super easy and automatically adds the og tags to your site to prevent the Facebook link preview not showing or showing the wrong thumbnail.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a look at how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"fixing-the-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-the-easy-way\">Fixing the Wrong Facebook Thumbnail (The Easy Way)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO The Best WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-23910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-the-best-wordpress-seo-plugin-and-toolkit-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An easy way to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress is by using the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">AIOSEO</a> plugin.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is a complete WordPress SEO plugin, which allows you to optimize your content for search engines and increase rankings with just a few clicks.&nbsp;It’s also great for optimizing your site for social media and making sure your thumbnails are showing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, you first need to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">install and activate AIOSEO</a> on your WordPress website. If you haven’t installed a plugin before, you can check out WPBeginner&#8217;s guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you need to enable Facebook thumbnail images for posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Facebook Thumbnails</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply go to <strong>Social Networks</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu, and then click on the <strong>Facebook</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"496\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"How to fix wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress - enable Facebook thumbnail settings in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24262\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/social-networks-menu-item-in-aioseo-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The first setting you’ll see is the <strong>Enable Open Graph Markup</strong>. Make sure it&#8217;s enabled.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"263\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-open-graph-markup-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Enable Open Graph Markup in general Facebook settings in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24263\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-open-graph-markup-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-open-graph-markup-in-aioseo-300x108.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/enable-open-graph-markup-in-aioseo-600x216.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The blue button means you’re all set!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to choose which thumbnail that’s used when your content is shared on Facebook.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Setting Facebook Thumbnail Image</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the <strong>Default Image Source</strong> setting, and it will give you a drop-down menu with different images sources to choose from.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/default-image-source-setting-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png\" alt=\"How to fix wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress - default image source setting in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-23296\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/default-image-source-setting-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/default-image-source-setting-in-all-in-one-seo-1-300x123.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/default-image-source-setting-in-all-in-one-seo-1-600x247.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see all images that exist for your site’s content, and you can choose the one you prefer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re not sure which one to choose, here’s a description of what the different image options mean:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Default Image</strong> – this will use the image set in the <a href=\"#default-facebook-image\">Default Facebook Image</a> setting.</li><li><strong>Featured Image</strong> – this will use the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/featured-image/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Featured Image</a>, which you set on your Posts and Pages whenever you publish a new Post or Page.</li><li><strong>First Attached Image</strong> – this will use the first image that’s <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/using-image-and-file-attachments/#attachment-to-a-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">attached to your Post or Page</a>.</li><li><strong>First Image in Content</strong> – this will use the first image that appears in the content of your Post or Page.</li><li><strong>Image from Custom Field</strong> – when you select this option, a <strong>Custom Field</strong> setting will be displayed where you can enter the name of the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/custom-fields/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Custom Field</a> you want to use for your image.</li><li><strong>Post Author Image</strong> – this will use the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/users-your-profile-screen/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Profile Picture</a> from the user profile for the author of the Post or Page.</li><li><strong>First Available Image</strong> – this will go through all of the above to look for an image to use</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this cleared things out for you, and that you now know which image source to choose for your Facebook thumbnail. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s move on to setting the default post Facebook thumbnail.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"default-facebook-image\">Setting Default Post Facebook Thumbnail</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After you’ve chosen which image source you want to use, you need to set a <strong>Default Post Facebook Image</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This image will be used as a reserve in case there’s no image available for your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you choose Featured Image<strong> </strong>in the Default Image Source drop-down, but your post or page doesn’t have a featured image, then AIOSEO will use what you’ve set as your Default Facebook Image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, if your theme allows you to add a logo, AIOSEO will automatically use the logo as your Default Post Facebook Image if you don’t set an Image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To set the Default Post Facebook Image, click on the <strong>Upload or Select Image</strong> button and upload your image, or choose an image from your Media Library.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"149\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/default-post-facebook-image-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Setting the default post Facebook image in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24264\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/default-post-facebook-image-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/default-post-facebook-image-in-aioseo-300x61.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/default-post-facebook-image-in-aioseo-600x122.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also type or paste in the URL for an image directly into the field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Facebook prefers images that are 1200px wide x 630px tall. The minimum dimensions are 200px x 200px. For more details, please visit Smash Baloon&#8217;s <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/ultimate-facebook-cheat-sheet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ultimate Facebook Cheat Sheet</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, let’s move on to how to change the Facebook thumbnail image on individual posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Setting Facebook Thumbnail on Individual Posts and Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also change the Facebook thumbnail on individual posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When editing your blog post or page, you simply scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> and then click on the <strong>Social </strong>tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure that you’ve clicked on the Facebook tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"726\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png\" alt=\"Setting Facebook thumbnail on individual posts and pages in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24266\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png 726w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-on-individual-posts-and-pages-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you need to scroll down past the Facebook Title and Description until you see the<strong> Image Source</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"291\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-image-source-facebook-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png\" alt=\"How to fix wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress - setting image source for Facebook thumbnail in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24267\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-image-source-facebook-on-individual-posts-and-pages.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-image-source-facebook-on-individual-posts-and-pages-300x120.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-image-source-facebook-on-individual-posts-and-pages-600x239.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the link, and it will display a drop-down menu. Here you can choose the image source for your individual post and pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s move on to setting your Facebook thumbnail for your homepage.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Setting Facebook Thumbnail on Your Home Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To set the Facebook thumbnail for your homepage, you need to scroll down in the <strong>General Facebook Settings</strong> to the <strong>Home Page Settings</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-home-page-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Setting Facebook thumbnail on your Home Page in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24268\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-home-page-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-home-page-in-aioseo-300x196.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/set-facebook-thumbnail-home-page-in-aioseo-600x392.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Image </strong>section, you simply click on the<strong> Upload or Select</strong> button to set your thumbnail image. This is the thumbnail that will be displayed when your homepage is shared on Facebook.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the image you choose will appear below the <strong>Image</strong> field, as well as in the <strong>Preview</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/upload-facebook-thumbnail-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Setting image for Facebook thumbnail on your Home Page in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-24269\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/upload-facebook-thumbnail-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/upload-facebook-thumbnail-in-aioseo-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/upload-facebook-thumbnail-in-aioseo-600x231.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve added your Facebook thumbnail image, you click on the <strong>Save </strong>button. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As simple as that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In most cases, this fixes the issue with Facebook showing the wrong thumbnail or none at all.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before leaving this topic, we also need to mention that you can set your <strong>Facebook Title</strong> and <strong>Facebook Description </strong>for your posts, pages, and homepage. If you want to know how to do this, please check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/setting-facebook-social-meta-for-your-homepage/#setting-the-facebook-social-meta-when-your-homepage-displays-your-latest-posts\">documentation here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, if Facebook still doesn’t show your thumbnail image, then you need to make sure you’ve <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-clear-your-cache-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">cleared your WordPress cache</a>.&nbsp;Or you can use Facebook’s debug tool to clear the cache. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a look at how to do that next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"using-facebook-debug-tool-to-clear-the-cache\">Using Facebook Debug Tool to Clear the Cache</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you know you’ve added the right thumbnail, and Facebook still isn’t showing any or the wrong one, then the issue is related to caching.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To solve this, the first thing you need to do is reset the cache in Facebook using their debug tool. It&#8217;s the easiest way to troubleshoot why Facebook shows the wrong thumbnail when you share a link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply copy the URL of your WordPress post and paste it in the Facebook debugger tool, and click on the <strong>Debug </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/facebook-debug-tool.png\" alt=\"How to fix wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress - Facebook\'s debugger tool\" class=\"wp-image-24272\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/facebook-debug-tool.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/facebook-debug-tool-300x170.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/facebook-debug-tool-600x340.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Facebook debugger tool will show you a warning symbol if something needs to be fixed, as well as tell you what you need to do to get your thumbnail to work.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, you can click on the <strong>Scrape Again</strong> button, and Facebook will update the thumbnail for your post.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this blog post helped you learn how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail in WordPress. You may also want to see our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress\">how to add Twitter Cards in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to optimize your blog post for SEO like a pro, make sure to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, we also give you tons of great tips on how to<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\"> improve search engine rankings</a> and<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\"> analyze your competitors’ SEO</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, thanks for supporting <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">the best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/\">How to Fix Wrong Facebook Thumbnail in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s